The paper introduces a new solution concept for game theory, which is relevant to the subfield of computational game theory (cs.GT). The concept involves iterated deletion of strategies, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses empirical observations and experiments, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI).
